5:
They just keep coming! Light,
something's wrong with this place!

many ghosts.
11:
...Oh, my! Quite the situation we
have here...
25:
You're the one who was calling in all

29:
...My name is Hildegarde. I've come

32:
Shall we go? I know exactly the

36:
My... Such beautiful dried flowers.
Don't worry anymore, I'll take care of
everything.
44:
...My apologies for all the
commotion. I'm Hildegarde of the
Memento Recovery Guild, and I
came to collect these dried flowers.
47:
Powerful feelings yet linger within
these flowers, which most likely
drew all those ghosts.
49:
Now that the memento has been
recovered, the ghosts shouldn't
appear anymore. 
At any rate, I'll be off now...
54:
Are you going to deliver those
flowers to someone?
58:
It would be a shame to simply
abandon them, no?
64:
Yes, indeed... You have a point.
These people hereâ€”

...Yes, let's do that. Are you ready to

83:
I'm from the Memento Recovery
Guild, and I'm here to deliver
something to you.
87:
Dried flowers...
They're... the same ones that I gave
to her...
91:
I-I know how she feels, okay?! My
wife blames me for what happened!
Those ghosts at the estate are proof
of that!
92:
I was off somewhere, busy doing
something stupid when that
criminal found her... I wasn't there for
her when she NEEDED me most!
95:
I see... I guess this time won't be any
different.
97:
I'm so sorry. But please, I want to

100: I already t-told you! S-stay back!
103: Do you think your wife blames you?
107:
Because when I found her, she said,
"I will watch over this house until I
can meet him one last time."
110:
That's why her spirit lingered. 
...Being with you again is all she
wanted.
113:
Th-that's... a lie...
You don't understand anything,
she'd never forgive me for what
happened...
116:
I see... But, even still... I need the
permission of the bereaved in order
to dispose of these flowers. Would
you mind just taking them for now?
118:
There won't be any more hauntings,
so you may do with these flowers

136:
...Heh-heh, about as well as I could
have asked for. I wasn't able to
convey her feelings to him... But this

138:
I've only ever known one other
person who could hear voices the
same as I. We're the strange ones,
without a doubt.
158:
Indeed. Despite what my age may
suggest, I serve as head of the
Memento Recovery Guild. My
apologies for not mentioning that
earlier.
165:
The people at the Guild. They're

169:
No need to worry. I recovered the
memento at the estate, so
everything will be fine now.
173:
...Did you do it. Alone? I know you're...
amazing. But still...
176:
Yes, I was concerned about the
danger of having anyone else
accompany me this time. But it's all
finished now.
180: I... see. In that case. I'm glad...
184:
You're acquainted with these folk, 
aren't you, Falsche? 
That makes things simpler.
187:
...Will you teach me how to visit
other worlds?
192: ...Can you tell us why you want to?
196:
Of course. You see, I want to retrieve
items that have been lost to shifts.
But in order to do that, I'd have to
visit the worlds that the items have
escaped into.
199:
I won't get in your way, as I can
recover the items by myself.
209:
...Thank you, Falsche. But I have my
own reasons for wanting to do this.
There's no need to for you to trouble

213:
But... I want to help. You're doing a...
good thing...
222:
Let's head out together. We
welcome you, Hildegarde.
226:
In that case, I'd be happy to receive
your help. Nothing dangerous
though, okay?
234:
I look forward to working with you
three, as well. I appreciate your
hospitality.
